race.comment: UNIVERSAL HOTNESS (6) stuck on well over 1000m first-up and landed there without a trial coming in. Sure to be fitter for that performance and out to 1200m now looks a good move. He hasn't won in a while, but he's knocking on the door of a drought breaking win and this looks a grand opportunity. LENIENCY (1) will be fitter for a recent trial coming in and boasts a solid fresh record. Turner knows the gelding well and he can land in a good spot from the barrier. Ticks a few boxes today and appears the main danger. THREE GRAND (4) comes here on the fresh side after a narrow win over this track and trip 69 days ago. Not been sighted since then, though she has the speed to roll across from out wide and she rates highly on that effort. Will be hard to run down. RUN PATTIE RUN (5) is better than we saw fresh and can improve. IMAPAGETHREE GIRL (7) looks ready to fire first-up judging by her recent trial.
